
[1]singly

   SIN'GLY, adv.

   1. Individually; particularly; as, to make men singly and personally
   good.

   2. Only; by himself. Look thee, 'tis so, thou singly honest man.

   3. Without partners, companions or associates; as, to attack another
   singly. At ombre singly to decide their doom.

   4. Honestly; sincerely.
